{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Replace GCSE and A-Level memory-based exams with open-book formats",
        "additional_details": "I think that changing to open-book exams could allow students to demonstrate deeper understanding and practical skills. In a world where information is easily accessible, I think education should focus on applying knowledge, not memorising it. This approach also promotes skills like note-taking and critical thinking.",
        "background": "I am a personal tutor with years of experience. I think that many bright students I work with struggle in exams due to poor memory, not lack of ability. This can lead to grades that don\u2019t reflect their potential or understanding, which I'm concerned can limit their future opportunities.",
